{
  "$comment": [
    "Crossfade tween snippet — pulled into composition.json via",
    "  { \"$ref\": \"./snippets/crossfades.json#/tweens\" }",
    "which selects the `tweens` array below; because the $ref sits inside an",
    "array context AND the resolved value is itself an array, the import",
    "resolver spreads the elements in place (see imports.ts walk: array+array =",
    "splice). Demonstrates §5 pointer mode + array-spread in one go.",
    "",
    "Each entry targets a scene-instance wrapper-group id (never an internal",
    "scene id) so the sealed-instance rule from §8.7 stays satisfied."
